**QA Lead / Test Architect (7+ years)** – Lead design and execution of an enterprise‑scale test strategy, oversee a team of 6+ automation and manual testers, and own end‑to‑end test governance across multiple product lines. Must architect reusable, component‑driven frameworks utilizing Playwright, Cypress.io, and RestAssured for web and API testing, and integrate fully with Azure DevOps Pipelines, GitLab CI/CD, and Harness to achieve continuous test delivery.  

Core responsibilities include:  
* Developing BDD/TDD test suites (Cucumber, SpecFlow) aligned with Agile/Scrum workflows;  
* Crafting performance test plans and executing load tests with JMeter and Gatling, reporting results to product, ops, and security stakeholders;  
* Instituting comprehensive test data management and data‑privacy controls compliant with ISO 27001 and SOC 2;  
* Mentoring staff on best practices, facilitating knowledge transfer, and setting metrics for test quality, coverage, and cycle time;  
* Collaborating with Security & Compliance to embed security testing (SAST, DAST, OWASP Top 10) into the CI pipeline;  
* Managing stakeholder expectations, preparing release‑readiness reviews, and integrating test results into Jira/Kanban boards for sprint planning.  

Requirements:  
* 7 + years of QA/Testing leadership experience, with 4 + years in automation;  
* Proven experience building test frameworks (Playwright, Selenium, Cypress, TestNG, JUnit, RestAssured) and interpreting results across multiple CI/CD environments;  
* Advanced knowledge of performance testing tools (JMeter, Gatling) and test data engineering;  
* ISO 27001 auditor or equivalent security testing credential (or strong security testing background) and PMP or equivalent project‑management certification;  
* Demonstrated ability to scale test operations within a regulated or highly‑audited industry;  
* U.S. work authorization or eligibility to obtain it, with readiness to be based in New York's corporate hub.  

Offer: full‑time, on‑site employment with a competitive salary range, performance bonuses, and a robust benefits package. Start date flexible.

