QA Test Analyst – 1‑3 years of experience in manual and exploratory testing with a strong foundation in test design and defect management (JIRA, Zephyr, TestRail).  
*Desired skills:*  
•  Knowledge of end‑to‑end web testing with Playwright 1.x (preferably ≥ 1.27) and optional Cypress 10+ for UI test automation;  
•  Experience writing API test scripts in Postman or REST‑assured (Java) and interpreting Swagger/OpenAPI specs;  
•  Basic proficiency in JavaScript/TypeScript (ES6+), with an understanding of async/await patterns for Playwright scripts;  
•  Familiarity with GitLab CI for running automated test suites and generating reports;  
•  Understanding of performance testing concepts (e.g., using k6 or Artillery™ for load testing small to medium traffic scenarios);  
•  BDD exposure (Gherkin/Cucumber) is a plus for writing readable acceptance criteria;  
•  Accessibility testing basics (WCAG 2.1) would be considered a plus.  
*Certification (optional but valued):* ISTQB Foundation Level or equivalent.  
*Culture & Logistics:* Agile Scrum team, mixed remote/hybrid work environment, candidate must be U.S.‑based or able to work the 8 h overlap with Eastern Time.  Ready to commence work within 2 weeks, bringing a proactive, detail‑oriented approach to test documentation and cross‑team collaboration.

