Senior Cybersecurity Engineer – Cloud Security & Vulnerability Management  

We are actively recruiting a seasoned Cybersecurity Engineer with 5–7 years of demonstrable expertise in cloud‑native security and vulnerability management. The successful candidate will be responsible for architecting, deploying, and continuously improving security controls across multi‑cloud environments (Azure, AWS, GCP), leveraging services such as Azure Security Center, AWS Security Hub, GuardDuty, and native container security tools (CIS Docker Bench, Aqua Security).  

Key responsibilities include:  
- Conducting automated vulnerability scans, penetration tests, and red‑team assessments on cloud infrastructure, Kubernetes clusters, and serverless workloads, using tools such as Qualys, Nessus, Kubescape, and open‑source pen‑testing frameworks;  
- Implementing secure CI/CD pipelines with integrated IaC security checks (Checkov, Terraform Sentinel);  
- Designing and enforcing dynamic access controls via least‑privilege IAM roles, IAM Policy Lab, and Cross‑Account Trust Federation;  
- Leading incident‑response exercises for cloud‑specific attacks (privilege escalation, data exfiltration, container escape) and ensuring rapid remediation;  
- Collaborating with DevOps, Cloud Architecture, and Governance teams to define and enforce security policies, compliance controls, and continuous monitoring dashboards.  

Required skills:  
- Proficiency with cloud security best practices, SOCIA, and defense‑in‑depth strategies;  
- Hands‑on experience with Azure AD, Okta, or other IAM solutions in a cloud context;  
- Strong configuration management knowledge (Terraform, CloudFormation, Ansible) and automated security tooling;  
- Certifications such as CISSP, Certified Cloud Security Professional (CCSP), or AWS/Azure Security Specialty are highly desirable;  
- Excellent analytical, communication, and stakeholder‑management abilities.  

This role is full‑time, located in our San Francisco office with a hybrid‑remote arrangement. Compensation will be commensurate with experience and the strategic value of the role.
